properties.headline: Marine Weather Statement issued February 19 at 3:26PM CST by NWS Corpus Christi TX
properties.description:
Moist onshore flow over the relatively cooler shelf waters will
lead to patchy to areas of sea fog through this evening.
Visibilities will generally range from 1 to 3 nautical miles,
with patchy dense fog of 1 nautical mile or less at times in bays
and nearshore waters.

Mariners over the Bay Waters and over the Nearshore Coastal
Waters within 20 nautical miles offshore are urged to prepare for
rapidly changing visibilities.

NWSheadline: PATCHY TO AREAS OF SEA FOG EXPECTED THIS EVENING ACROSS THE BAYS AND NEARSHORE WATERS
